Hi,

When rendering RestructuredText, headers with particular names will be mis-aligned. Here is an [example|https://bitbucket.org/const_dev/rest-display-issue/src/ad98e933a00c48beaa6e6ae304f2f75dd06f1592/README.rst%3Fat%3Dmaster] shows that the header "Features" is shifted right by several pixels comparing to other headers in the same level.

I think this has something to do with the generated HTML:

{code}
#!html

<div class="section" id="features">
<h2>Features</h2>
<p>test</p>
</div>
{code}

where the id {{features}} happens to be defined in this [CSS file|https://d3oaxc4q5k2d6q.cloudfront.net/m/d30fd04b3391/compressed/css/ddaf242a17f4.css] used in the HTML:

{code}
#!css

#features {
  margin: 20px 0;
  padding: 0 10px;
}
{code}

By the way, markdown does not have the same issue.

Thanks.

In the overview tab of a Team owned repository, commits are shown as:\\
{{<<TEAM>> pushed 1 commit to <<REPO>>}} instead of {{<<MEMBER> pushed 1 commit o <<REPO>>}}

The commits tab correctly identifies the team member who pushed the commit, however.  This makes recent activity less useful if there are only one or two repos, as the information of _who_ is missing.

Can&#x27;t work multiple fixture issue closing in commit comment. Example:

{code}
fix: BCLOUD-39
fix: BCLOUD-40
{code}
